column4:
The American
Academy of Pediatrics recommends
that children should watch no more than 2 hours of television per day.1 Our
current findings are consistent with
this advice. Reductions in habitual television
viewing may assist with limiting
the susceptibility of children to television
advertising messages for energydense
foods and therefore help to improve
their diet and health.
